description:
Watch as the story of Joseph from Genesis chapter 39 and Genesis chapter 40 comes to life in iBIBLEthe worlds first visual and interactive Bible. Featured in the 31st episode of iBIBLE is the story of Joseph as he works as a faithful servant in Egypt. Potiphar, who bought Joseph, is an officer of Pharaoh. Joseph is successful in all that he does and is set over his masters house and all that he has. Potiphars wife notices Joseph, and asks him to come to bed with her, but he flees. Potiphars wife accuses Joseph, and he is put in prison. Study the Biblical Narrative and enjoy this presentation of Gods Word with iBIBLE.

A production of RevelationMedia, iBIBLE brings Gods Word to life in a format that people all over the world can engage with. Through dramatic audio and vibrant animation, people of all ages, all backgrounds, and with all abilities can learn the Biblical narrativethe one cohesive story of Scripture. iBIBLE will be available for free to translate into any of the worlds 7,000+ languages. Join the movement today and help bring the true story of Gods Word to the nations for free!

Visit www.iBIBLE.app to see all completed episodes of iBIBLEa visual Bible for a visual and connected world! 

Director: Steve Cleary
